    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is accepted because the ASTM F1717 standard specifies a single canonical test geometry and the analytical sensitivity estimate indicates less than 8% QoI variation across the plausible offset range. Overall credibility is sufficient to support the regulatory decision at Medium model risk. Decision: Accepted.",
